INSERT INTO contributions (idea_id, author_id, content, decision_log, status, view_count, submitted_at, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
(11, 7, E'# RecallIQ \x2014 Dental Patient Recall Automation Platform\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nRecallIQ is a HIPAA-compliant SaaS platform purpose-built for independent dental practices with 500\xe2\x80\x932,000 active patients. It automates the entire recall workflow\xe2\x80\x94sending multi-channel reminders via SMS, email, and automated voice calls\xe2\x80\x94while giving front-desk staff a live dashboard to track no-show rates, overdue patients, and hygiene chair utilization. Independent practices lose an estimated $42,000 per year per hygienist in unfilled recall appointments. RecallIQ reduces no-show rates by 35\xe2\x80\x9345% and fills cancellation gaps within hours through an intelligent waitlist engine, directly recovering revenue that currently walks out the door.\n\n**Core Value Proposition**: Turn your recall list from a chore into a revenue engine. Zero phone tag, zero manual tracking, zero missed cleanings.\n\n**Year-1 Goals**:\n- 250 active practice subscriptions\n- Average 38% reduction in no-show rate per enrolled practice\n- MRR of $62,500 by month 12\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Data | Source / Notes |\n|--------|------|----------------|\n| Independent dental practices (US) | ~107,000 | ADA 2023 Workforce Report |\n| Practices with 500\xe2\x80\x932,000 active patients | ~58,000 | Estimated 54% of total |\n| Average hygiene appointments/year per practice | 1,800\xe2\x80\x932,400 | Industry benchmark |\n| Revenue per hygiene appointment | $150\xe2\x80\x93$220 | National average |\n| No-show / unfilled recall rate (industry avg) | 18\xe2\x80\x9323% | Dental Economics 2023 |\n| Annual revenue lost per practice | $38,000\xe2\x80\x93$52,000 | Calculated from above |\n| Practices using dedicated recall software | <22% | Dental Products Report survey |\n| TAM (dedicated recall SaaS) | ~$348M/year | 58,000 \xd7 $500/mo avg |\n| SAM (reachable via digital channels) | ~$104M/year | 30% addressable |\n| Year-1 SOM | ~$750K | 250 practices \xd7 $250/mo |\n\n**Key Trends**:\n- Post-COVID patient reactivation backlogs created urgency for automated outreach\n- Two-way SMS recall preferred by patients under 45 (68% response rate vs 12% for phone)\n- DSOs (Dental Service Organizations) growing but independent practices still 61% of market\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Product | Positioning | Monthly Price | Recall Automation | No-Show Analytics | HIPAA Compliant | Key Weakness |\n|---------|-------------|---------------|-------------------|-------------------|-----------------|--------------|\n| Lighthouse 360 | Full dental marketing suite | $349\xe2\x80\x93$499 | Yes | Basic | Yes | Expensive, slow onboarding |\n| Solutionreach | Enterprise patient engagement | $400\xe2\x80\x93$600 | Yes | Moderate | Yes | Overkill for small practices |\n| Weave | Phone + messaging platform | $400\xe2\x80\x93$550 | Partial | Weak | Yes | Primary focus is VoIP, not recall |\n| RevenueWell | Marketing automation | $299\xe2\x80\x93$450 | Yes | Moderate | Yes | Complex setup, long contracts |\n| Doctible | Reviews + recall | $199\xe2\x80\x93$299 | Basic | None | Yes | Recall is secondary feature |\n| **RecallIQ** | **Recall-first, simple UI** | **$149\xe2\x80\x93$249** | **Advanced** | **Deep** | **Yes** | **New brand** |\n\n**Competitive Conclusion**: Existing solutions bundle recall into large suites at premium prices. RecallIQ wins on focus, simplicity, and price point\xe2\x80\x94the three things independent practice owners care about most.\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n### Persona A: Solo-Practice Owner \xe2\x80\x94 Dr. Karen Schultz\n- **Age**: 48, female, owns a 2-chair practice in suburban Ohio\n- **Patient Panel**: 780 active patients, 1 full-time hygienist\n- **Current Recall Process**: Front desk manually calls patients 3 days before appointments; uses a paper recall binder\n- **Pain Points**:\n  1. Front desk spends 2\xe2\x80\x933 hours/day on recall calls with a 30% answer rate\n  2. 19% no-show rate costs her ~$39,000/year in lost hygiene revenue\n  3. Patients who cancel are not rebooked\xe2\x80\x94the slot just stays empty\n- **Quote**: "I need to fill the chair, not chase people by phone all morning."\n- **Willingness to Pay**: $149\xe2\x80\x93$199/month; ROI must be obvious in 60 days\n\n### Persona B: Office Manager \xe2\x80\x94 Michelle Torres\n- **Age**: 35, manages front desk for a 4-chair group practice in Texas\n- **Patient Panel**: 1,650 active patients, 3 hygienists\n- **Pain Points**:\n  1. Juggling three hygienists\xe2\x80\x99 recall schedules in separate spreadsheets\n  2. No visibility into which hygienist has the worst no-show rate\n  3. Current software (Dentrix) has recall but it requires manual export/import\n- **Goal**: Reduce her daily recall call burden by 80% and show the dentist a monthly report\n- **Willingness to Pay**: $229\xe2\x80\x93$249/month for multi-provider dashboard\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Feature | Priority | Description |\n|---------|----------|-------------|\n| Automated SMS/email recall sequences | P0 | 3-touch sequence: 30 days, 7 days, 1 day before due date |\n| Two-way SMS confirmation | P0 | Patients confirm, cancel, or request reschedule via text |\n| No-show rate dashboard | P0 | Per-hygienist, per-period, trend line |\n| Overdue patient list (90/180/365 days) | P0 | Filterable list with one-click re-engage |\n| Intelligent waitlist engine | P1 | Auto-texts waitlist when cancellation occurs |\n| PMS integration (Dentrix, Eaglesoft, Open Dental) | P1 | Bi-directional sync every 15 min |\n| Automated voice call fallback | P1 | AI voice call if SMS unread after 48 hrs |\n| Multi-provider scheduling view | P1 | Color-coded hygienist chair utilization |\n| Patient reactivation campaign builder | P2 | Bulk outreach for patients inactive 18+ months |\n| Google review request after appointment | P2 | Auto-send review link post-visit |\n| Customizable message templates | P2 | Practice-branded SMS/email copy |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n**Backend**: Go 1.22 + PostgreSQL 17 (HIPAA-compliant RDS with encryption at rest and in transit). All PHI stored with AES-256 encryption. BAA agreements with all sub-processors.\n\n**Messaging Layer**: Twilio for SMS/voice, SendGrid for email. Message queue via Redis + BullMQ for reliable delivery with retry logic.\n\n**PMS Integration**: RESTful adapter pattern with connectors for Dentrix G7+, Eaglesoft 21+, Open Dental 23+. Nightly full sync + 15-min delta sync.\n\n**Frontend**: Next.js 15 + TailwindCSS 4. Mobile-first dashboard optimized for front-desk use on tablets.\n\n**Infrastructure**: AWS us-east-1 (HIPAA eligible). ECS Fargate containers, RDS Multi-AZ, CloudFront CDN. SOC 2 Type II audit planned for Q3.\n\n**Security**: OAuth 2.0 SSO, role-based access (dentist / office manager / front desk), full audit log of all PHI access, automatic session timeout.\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Plan | Price/Month | Patient Cap | Providers | Key Features |\n|------|-------------|-------------|-----------|------|\n| Solo | $149 | Up to 800 patients | 1 provider | SMS + email recall, basic dashboard |\n| Practice | $229 | Up to 1,500 patients | Up to 3 providers | + voice fallback, waitlist engine, PMS sync |\n| Growth | $299 | Up to 2,500 patients | Up to 6 providers | + reactivation campaigns, review requests, API access |\n| Enterprise | Custom | Unlimited | Unlimited | DSO multi-location, custom integrations, dedicated CSM |\n\n**Additional Revenue**:\n- Setup / onboarding fee: $299 one-time (waived for annual plans)\n- SMS overage: $0.015/message above plan cap\n- PMS integration add-on (non-standard systems): $49/month\n\n**Unit Economics (Practice Plan)**:\n- CAC: ~$380 (content + PLG + dental conference sponsorship)\n- LTV at 28-month avg retention: ~$6,412\n- LTV:CAC ratio: ~16.9x\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Milestone | Timeline | Deliverables |\n|-----------|----------|--------------|\n| M1 | Weeks 1\xe2\x80\x934 | Core recall engine (SMS + email), manual patient import CSV, basic no-show dashboard, Twilio + SendGrid integration |\n| M2 | Weeks 5\xe2\x80\x938 | Two-way SMS confirmation, overdue patient list, Open Dental PMS sync, HIPAA BAA framework |\n| M3 | Weeks 9\xe2\x80\x9312 | Waitlist engine, voice call fallback, Dentrix + Eaglesoft sync, multi-provider view |\n| M4 | Weeks 13\xe2\x80\x9316 | Reactivation campaign builder, Google review requests, Stripe billing, self-serve onboarding |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | Baseline | Month-3 Target | Month-12 Target |\n|-----|----------|----------------|------------------|\n| Active paying practices | 0 | 40 | 250 |\n| Avg no-show rate reduction (enrolled practices) | 0% | 28% | 38% |\n| Monthly Recurring Revenue | $0 | $8,200 | $62,500 |\n| Net Revenue Retention | \xe2\x80\x94 | \xe2\x80\x94 | >108% |\n| PMS sync uptime | \xe2\x80\x94 | 99.5% | 99.9% |\n| Avg onboarding time to first recall sent | \xe2\x80\x94 | <2 hrs | <45 min |\n| NPS | \xe2\x80\x94 | >45 | >60 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| HIPAA compliance violation | Low | Critical | Hire HIPAA compliance officer in M1; quarterly audits; cyber liability insurance |\n| PMS vendor API changes breaking sync | Medium | High | Adapter pattern isolates connectors; automated regression tests; 48-hr hotfix SLA |\n| Low SMS deliverability (carrier filtering) | Medium | High | Use 10DLC registered numbers; A2P campaign registration; fallback to email + voice |\n| Incumbent (Lighthouse 360) price war | Medium | Medium | Compete on simplicity + support, not price; target practices that already rejected incumbents |\n| Practice churns after no-show rate improves | Low | Medium | Expand value with reactivation campaigns and review management to increase stickiness |\n| Slow PMS integration adoption | Medium | Medium | Offer free CSV import as always-on fallback; prioritize top 3 PMS systems covering 78% of market |',
 E'[{"step": 1, "action": "Market sizing", "rationale": "Quantified the no-show revenue loss per practice to anchor ROI conversation; $42K/year makes $249/mo an easy sale."}, {"step": 2, "action": "Competitive audit", "rationale": "Found all incumbents priced $300-$600/mo and bundled into large suites; clear opening for a focused, affordable alternative."}, {"step": 3, "action": "Persona development", "rationale": "Interviewed 8 dental office managers via Zoom; discovered the front desk, not the dentist, is the actual buyer for recall software."}, {"step": 4, "action": "PMS integration scoping", "rationale": "Dentrix + Eaglesoft + Open Dental cover 78% of independent practices; prioritized these three for M2-M3."}, {"step": 5, "action": "HIPAA architecture review", "rationale": "Confirmed AWS HIPAA-eligible services cover all PHI storage requirements; BAA agreements needed with Twilio and SendGrid before launch."}, {"step": 6, "action": "Pricing validation", "rationale": "Tested $149/$229/$299 tiers with 12 prospects; $229 Practice plan had highest purchase intent for target segment."}]',
 'submitted', 52,
 NOW() - INTERVAL '28 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '28 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '28 days');

